HEADWORD: weeping tree broom
<hw>weeping tree broom</hw> <pos>n.</pos> <def>a small shrubby tree of
New Zealand having weeping branches and racemes of white to violet
flowers followed by woolly indehiscent 2-seeded pods.</def>⟦br⟧
<note> a broom is any of various shrubs of the genera Cytisus or Genista
or Spartium having long slender branches and racemes of yellow
flowers.</note>⟦br⟧
[<source>WordNet 1.5</source>]</p>

